	   <tr><td colspan=2>First, let me say that I have both a Druid and a Shaman and I love playing them both.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>HOWEVER, I get extremely tired of complete strangers wandering up to me asking for SoW "ALL THE TIME" ! ! !  If you refuse, some will politely go on their way.  Some...  Others get all pissy about it like you owe it to the world to SoW everyone who walks up to you and requests/demands it!<br><br>After CONSTANT requests for SoW "everytime" I play, many times I just don't want to hear it anymore...  I would imagine that people may "interpret" that as being stand-offish, not realizing that the SoW that they just asked for was preceeded by umpteen zillion previous request that same night prior to their asking...  <br><br>This is not to forget that with every class there are advantages and trade-offs associated with that particular choice.  If SoW is so important to you, then you should play Druid or Shaman!  This was a major factor in my choices, and I gave up other benefits to play these two classes.  Do not expect ANY sympathy from me because you don't have SoW.  You choose your class for the advantages that it offers.  Live with your choice!!!  Don't expect me to be the one to let you "have your cake and eat it too" by constantly SoWing you whenever you ask/demand it...!!!<br><br>Please note, however, group members are a different story altogether.  I will "ALWAYS" SoW members of my group.  I feel that is part of my contribution and role within the group.  If you want SoW from us (Druids/Shaman) then try inviting us into your group...!<br><br>Just my 2 cents worth.<br><br>Kanu, 19th lvl Shaman<br>Kega, 12th lvl Druid <br>(and yes, I still get asked for SoW all the time even though I am unable to cast it yet...!!!)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
